ut sprocket as it is raised.","Insert the left hand front cylinder bolt (12), do not tighten at this stage.","Insert the right hand front cylinder head bolt and fit the nut (6).","Lubricate the threads of the mounting bolts for the cylinder head rear mountings "," only"," with a smear of proprietary high temperature copper based grease.","Apply a smear of proprietary high temperature copper based grease to the threads of the right hand rear cylinder head bolt (1), fit but do not fully tighten. ","Apply a smear of proprietary high temperature copper based grease to the threads of the left hand rear cylinder head bolt (7), do not tighten at this stage. ","Insert the lower crankcase bolt (9) through lower crankcase from right hand side, fit the spacer (3).","Spacer","Insert the upper crankcase bolt (11) through upper crankcase from right hand side.","Fit and tighten the right hand front cylinder head bolt (6) to ","24 Nm",".","The frame is fitted with four frame adjuster sleeves, located on the left hand side of the frame, as shown below.","Using ","service tool T3880103",", tighten the left hand upper crankcase adjuster (5) to ","10 Nm",". ","Using ","service tool T3880181",", tighten the left hand lower crankcase adjuster(4) to ","10 Nm",".","T3880103 - Engine Mounting Adjuster","Rear upper frame adjuster","T3880181 - Wrench Frame Adjuster","Rear lower frame adjuster","Remove the bolt (12) from left hand front cylinder head mount and tighten the adjuster (10) to ","3 Nm",".","T3880103 - Engine Mounting Adjuster","Front frame adjuster","Remove the bolt (7) from left hand rear cylinder head mount and Tighten the adjuster (2) to ","3 Nm",". ","Front frame adjuster position","Centre frame adjuster position","Rear upper frame adjuster position","Rear lower frame adjuster position","Apply a smear of proprietary high temperature copper based grease to the threads of the left hand rear cylinder head bolt (7), fit and torque to ","48 Nm",".","Fit the bolt and a new locknut (12) though the left hand front cylinder head mount. ","Fit the washer and a new lock nut (9) to the upper and lower crankcase bolt (11), do not tighten at this stage. ","Tighten the right hand rear cylinder head bolt (1) to ","48 Nm",". ","Tighten the left hand rear cylinder head bolt (7) to ","48 Nm",".","Hold the lower crankcase mount bolt (9) and tighten the new lock nut to ","48 Nm",". ","Hold the upper crankcase mount bolt(11) and tighten the new lock nut to ","48 Nm",". ","Tighten the left hand front cylinder head bolt (12) to ","48 Nm",".","Tighten the right hand front cylinder head bolt (6) to ","48 Nm",".","Connect the clutch cable to the clutch (see ","Clutch Cable - Installation",").","Connect the crankshaft position sensor to the main harness.","Crankshaft position sensor connector","Route the alternator harness as noted for removal and connect it to the regulator/rectifier.","Regulator/rectifier","Grey connector","Black connector","Attach the ground cables to the engine and tighten the fixing to ","10 Nm",". Refit the rubber boot over the ground cables.","Attach the two harness brackets and purge valve bracket to the engine breather cover and tighten the fixings to ","10 Nm",".","Harness brackets","Fixings","Rubber boot","Ground cable fixing","Purge valve bracket (purge valve shown removed for clarity)","Connect the gear position sensor to the main harness.","Reconnect all electrical connections to the engine.","Align the split line on the gear pedal crank to the dot mark on gear change shaft. Tighten the pinch bolt to ","8 Nm",".","Dot mark","Split line","Pinch bolt","Refit the gear selector rod. Make sure the wire clip locates correctly in the ball joint, before rotating the clip to lock in place.","Ball joint","Wire clip","Set the drive chain adjustment (see ","Final Drive Chain Free-Movement Adjustment",").","Route the side stand switch down to the side stand as noted for removal.","Side stand switch electrical connector","front sprocket cover","Side stand switch harness","Hose","Oxygen sensor lead","If drained, refill the engine with new oil (see ","Oil and Oil Filter Change",").","Perform the following operations:","Exhaust Header Pipe - Installation","Exhaust Front Silencer - Installation","Exhaust Rear Silencer - Installation","Coolant expansion Tank - Installation","Radiator - Installation","Side Stand Switch - Installation","Front Sprocket Cover - Installation","Throttle Bodies/Injectors - Installation","Airbox - Installation","Fuel Tank - Installation","Alternator Regulator/Rectifier - Installation","Fairings - Installation","Battery - Reconnection","Riders Seat - Installation"],"viewCount":0,"infoType":"InfoType08","views":[],"createdAt":"2024-01-18T12:24:04.960Z","updatedAt":"2024-01-18T12:24:04.960Z","__v":0}